e of technical market\nconditions after the rise of points\nin a week even if there had been no\nlabor troubles.\nProgre\u00abs Wade\nWhile labor troubles continued.\nprogress was made thia week in the\nlabor situation. Each day it became\nclearer that managers of steel corpo\nrations bad no intention of granting\nwage increases demanded by the CIO\nand sponsored by President Truman\nunless selling prices were raised to\noffset whatever increase is granted\nin wages. That is progress because\nthe original attitude of both the CIO\nand the administration was that\nwages could be increased without\nraising selling prices, and now the\nadministration realizes that, to get\nneeded industrial production, selling\nj prices must be raised along with\ni wages; that otherwise production will\nlag. manufacturers being unwilling to\nturn out goods without a profit.\nAll of which increases the over\nhanging threat of more inflation.\nw\nSalM in IO0\u00ab High Low Oo\u00ab\u00ab Chg.\n9 Stand Brands 49% 48% 48%\u2014\nI Mpf 114 IM 114\n2H Srd GAE >4 pf 41% 40% 41%+\n3 Do 16 pr pf ~127% 127 127\n5 Do S7pr pf ..137% 137 137%\u2014\n31 Stand Dil Cal 47% 46% 47%+\n11 Stand OH Ind 42 41% 42\n34 Stand Oil N J 68% <7% 68%+\n6 Stand OH Ohio 28% 23% 23%\u2014\n18 Std Stl Sprg 25% 23 23%+\n2 Kt arret t tLS) W% 48 48%+ 1%\n4 Sterling Drug 45% 4a 45%+\n44 Stewart-Wa.ro 24% 23% 24%+\n28 btokely-VanCamp 35 33% 36 +2\n2 Do pf 22% 22%\n6 Stone A Webster 22 21% 22\n15 Studebaker Corp 32% 32% 32%+\n87 Sun Cbem 2\u2019)% 19% 20%+\n5 Sun OU 45% 65% \u00ab5%+\n.90 Sun Chern pf ..108% 107% I<\u00bb7%\u2014\n47 Sunray Oil 9% 9 9\n62 Sunshine Mng 23% 22% 23%+\n9 Superheater 34% 34 34%\n1 Sup OH Cal ~..13\u00ab\u00bb 13D 130\n1 Superior Steel 30% 50% 1\n1 Sutherland Pap 39%| 39% 3\u00bb%+\n18 Swift A Co 41% 40% 41%+\n11 Swift Inti +5% 34% 35% J*\n10 Svlvan El Prod 38% 38% 38%\n26 Syming-Gould 16% 15% 16%\n_T\n5 Talcott (J) Inc 15% 14% 14%\u2014\n3 Telautograph 12% 12% 12%\n11 Tenn Corp 19% 19 I\u00bb%+\